the 2009 military coup d'état that led to the absolute loss of democratic values. The election results of November 27, 2009, were celebrated as a great triumph in free elections and democracy. As President Zelaya was attempting to abolish State institutions and legalize his re-election to a new constitutional term, the National Congress expelled him from the presidency. It was in an attempt to curb electoral fraud and create true representation of the population. Since then, Honduras has gone from crisis to crisis; our Golden Child, democracy, lost its recognition. We are heading towards becoming a dictatorship, with economic and political tyrants breaking through democratic mechanisms and wanting to establish an "Endarto" style of government, that supported the De la Madrid administration in Mexico.

Does Central America have great potential for all sectors? What are the prospects in projects, for example, tourism and hospitality sector?

Central America is at the brink of a phenomenon that is its biggest opportunity. The explanation goes all the way back to the Second Spanish Colonial Period in the 1600s. The thirteen colonies of the Americas were experiencing rapid economic growth and had reached a stage where slavery was generating a growth in commerce that entered into a collapse. If you look at world history, you will notice that so great was that moment that the Spanish Crown lost its strength. Some of those colonies became independent and the one that flourished the most was the United States of America.
